cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.PL

The paper discusses techniques for secure computation on encrypted data, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The use of homomorphic encryption and secure enclaves like Intel's SGX suggests a focus on cryptography (cs.CR) and hardware security (cs.SE). The implementation of a transformed neural network for machine learning suggests a focus on data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of a Java bytecode-to-bytecode compiler suggests a focus on programming languages (cs.PL).
